2026-03-07 14:07:19 - aiosqlite - DEBUG - executing functools.partial(<built-in method execute of sqlite3.Connection object at 0x0000020595C11990>, 'INSERT INTO library_documents \n                (id, category, name, icon, description, content, tags, agents, created_at, updated_at)\n                VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)', ('842b8a34-b7e1-4410-b9a6-1e23c26f847c', 'libraries', 'pathlib', '📂', 'Manipulation de chemins de fichiers Python — Path, glob, read/write', '# pathlib — Référence rapide\n\n## Créer un chemin\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\npath = Path("data/file.txt")\nabs_path = Path.cwd() / "data" / "file.txt"\n\n## Vérifications\nif path.exists():\n    print("Existe")\nif path.is_file():\n    print("Fichier")\nif path.is_dir():\n    print("Dossier")\n\n## Lire/Écrire\ncontent = path.read_text()\npath.write_text("nouveau contenu")\n\n## Navigation\nparent = path.parent\nname = path.name\nstem = path.stem  # sans extension\nsuffix = path.suffix  # extension\n\n## Créer dossiers\npath.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n## Glob (recherche)\nfor file in Path(".").glob("*.py"):\n    print(file)\n\nfor file in Path(".").rglob("*.py"):  # récursif\n    print(file)', '["python", "filesystem"]', '["CODEUR"]', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.537350', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.537350'))
2026-03-07 14:07:19 - aiosqlite - DEBUG - operation functools.partial(<built-in method execute of sqlite3.Connection object at 0x0000020595C11990>, 'INSERT INTO library_documents \n                (id, category, name, icon, description, content, tags, agents, created_at, updated_at)\n                VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)', ('842b8a34-b7e1-4410-b9a6-1e23c26f847c', 'libraries', 'pathlib', '📂', 'Manipulation de chemins de fichiers Python — Path, glob, read/write', '# pathlib — Référence rapide\n\n## Créer un chemin\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\npath = Path("data/file.txt")\nabs_path = Path.cwd() / "data" / "file.txt"\n\n## Vérifications\nif path.exists():\n    print("Existe")\nif path.is_file():\n    print("Fichier")\nif path.is_dir():\n    print("Dossier")\n\n## Lire/Écrire\ncontent = path.read_text()\npath.write_text("nouveau contenu")\n\n## Navigation\nparent = path.parent\nname = path.name\nstem = path.stem  # sans extension\nsuffix = path.suffix  # extension\n\n## Créer dossiers\npath.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n## Glob (recherche)\nfor file in Path(".").glob("*.py"):\n    print(file)\n\nfor file in Path(".").rglob("*.py"):  # récursif\n    print(file)', '["python", "filesystem"]', '["CODEUR"]', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.537350', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.537350')) completed
