2026-03-07 14:07:19 - aiosqlite - DEBUG - executing functools.partial(<built-in method execute of sqlite3.Connection object at 0x0000020595C11990>, 'INSERT INTO library_documents \n                (id, category, name, icon, description, content, tags, agents, created_at, updated_at)\n                VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)', ('98536231-db5b-46dd-9540-263a8d92c414', 'libraries', 'JSON', '📄', 'Manipulation JSON Python — load, dump, dumps, loads', '# JSON — Référence rapide\n\n## Lire depuis fichier\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nwith open("data.json") as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\n# Ou avec pathlib\ndata = json.loads(Path("data.json").read_text())\n\n## Écrire dans fichier\nwith open("data.json", "w") as f:\n    json.dump(data, f, indent=2)\n\n# Ou avec pathlib\nPath("data.json").write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2))\n\n## String → Dict\njson_string = \'{"key": "value"}\'\ndata = json.loads(json_string)\n\n## Dict → String\ndata = {"key": "value"}\njson_string = json.dumps(data, indent=2)\n\n## Options utiles\njson.dumps(data, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False, sort_keys=True)', '["python", "data", "serialization"]', '["CODEUR"]', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.674476', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.674476'))
2026-03-07 14:07:19 - aiosqlite - DEBUG - operation functools.partial(<built-in method execute of sqlite3.Connection object at 0x0000020595C11990>, 'INSERT INTO library_documents \n                (id, category, name, icon, description, content, tags, agents, created_at, updated_at)\n                VALUES (?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?, ?)', ('98536231-db5b-46dd-9540-263a8d92c414', 'libraries', 'JSON', '📄', 'Manipulation JSON Python — load, dump, dumps, loads', '# JSON — Référence rapide\n\n## Lire depuis fichier\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nwith open("data.json") as f:\n    data = json.load(f)\n\n# Ou avec pathlib\ndata = json.loads(Path("data.json").read_text())\n\n## Écrire dans fichier\nwith open("data.json", "w") as f:\n    json.dump(data, f, indent=2)\n\n# Ou avec pathlib\nPath("data.json").write_text(json.dumps(data, indent=2))\n\n## String → Dict\njson_string = \'{"key": "value"}\'\ndata = json.loads(json_string)\n\n## Dict → String\ndata = {"key": "value"}\njson_string = json.dumps(data, indent=2)\n\n## Options utiles\njson.dumps(data, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False, sort_keys=True)', '["python", "data", "serialization"]', '["CODEUR"]', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.674476', '2026-03-07T14:07:19.674476')) completed
